s under another of his pseudonyms jill emerson the first of his work to appear under his own name was the  story you cant lose for the crimeadventure magazine manhunt he has since published more than fifty novels and more than a hundred short stories as well as a series of books for writers block has lived in new york city for decades setting most of his fiction there and has come to be very closely associated with the city he is married to lynne block he has three daughters amy reichel jill block and alison pouliot from an earlier marriage with lynne he spends much of his time traveling the two have been to  countries but continues to consider new york his home he was a regular guest on the late late show with craig ferguson  appearing in eight of fergusons ten seasons as host of the program considerable autobiographical information on the earlier phase of his life and career may be found scattered through telling lies for fun and profit  a collection of his fiction columns from writers digest in  he was honored with the gumshoe lifetime achievement award block is an alumnus of the ragdale foundation matthew scudderedit main article matthew scudder blocks most famous creation the everevolving matthew scudder was introduced in s the sins of the fathers as an alcoholic excop working as an unlicensed private investigator in hells kitchen originally published as paperbacks the early novels are interchangeable the second and third entries—in the midst of death  and time to murder and create —were written in the opposite order s  million ways to die filmed in  by hal ashby with unpopular results breaks from that trend concluding with scudder introducing himself at an alcoholics anonymous meeting the series was set to end on that note but an idle promise block had made to supply an editor friend with an original scudder short resulted in by the dawns early light a story set during the characters drinking days but told from the perspective of a recovering alcoholic block expanded on that with s when the sacred ginmill closes named for a line in a song by folk singer dave van ronk a close friend which proved not only one of the more literary entries but also a favorite of the author and his fans from then on scudders circumstances rarely remain the same from one book to the next s a ticket to the boneyard for example reunites him with elaine mardell a hooker from his days on the force whom he marries several books later other fan favorites are s taut gruesome a dance at the slaughterhouse winner of the edgar award for best mystery novel and s a long line of dead men a tightly plotted puzzler featuring a rapidly dwindling fraternity known as the club of  a walk among the tombstones published in  was made into a film released in  written and directed by scott frank with liam neeson playing the lead role the seventeenth entry a drop of the hard stuff was published in may  it has been suggested that scudders struggle with alcoholism is in part autobiographical while block has repeatedly refused to discuss the subject citing aas own tradition of anonymity in a column he wrote for writers digest block wrote that when he created scudder i let him hang out in the same saloon where i spent a great deal of my own time i was drinking pretty heavily around that time and i made him a pretty heavy drinker too i drank whiskey sometimes mixing it with coffee so did scudder bernie rhodenbarredit main article bernie rhodenbarr blocks other major series humorous and much lighter in tone relates the misadventures of gentleman burglar bernie rhodenbarr the series is rich in sophisticated witty dialogue unlike scudder rhodenbarr is ageless remaining essentially the same from s burglars cant be choosers to the eleventh and most recent entry s the burglar who counted the spoons the only significant advancements come in the third volume the burglar who liked to quote kipling  winner of the first annual nero award which sees bernie having used the spoils from his previous caper to buy a bookstore and introduces carolyn kaiser his lesbian soulmate and partner in crime the plots run very much to form bernie breaks into a residence usually on manhattans upper east side and through a series of implausible events becomes involved in a murder investigation—often as the prime suspect not even an elevenyear hiatus between s the burglar who painted like mondrian and s the burglar who traded ted williams would see that basic formula change there is however a meta quality to the more recent entries bernie the reluctant detective is himself a bookseller and genre fan and is apt to make references to agatha christie ew hornung his cat is named raffles dashiell hammett raymond chandler sue grafton and john sandford among others the burglar who thought he was bogart  exploits this to full effect set during a humphrey bogart film festival the story is itself inspired by many of the actors most famous roles the burglar in the library  similarly imagines a meeting between hammet and chandler at a new england inn in the s casting a volume inscribed by chandler to hammett as its own maltese falcon in the burglar in the rye bernie helps track down a writer clearly based on jd salinger the second novel the burglar in the closet was filmed in  as burglar with whoopi goldberg as bernie or bernice evan michael tanneredit main article evan michael tanner besides scudder and rhodenbarr block has written eight novels about evan tanner an adventurer and accidental revolutionary who as a result of an injury sustained in the korean war cannot sleep all but the last of these were published in the s and early s beginning with s the thief who couldnt sleep while the most recent s tanner on ice revived the character after nearly a thirtyyear hiatus chip harrisonedit chip harrison running on the twin engines of lust and curiosity originally appeared in two funny nonmystery novels which revolved around seventeenyearold chips obsessive quest to lose his virginity no score and chip harrison scores again realizing the series didnt have much of a future once chip reached his goal block puts chip to work as an assistant to leo haig an admirer of sleuth nero wolfe who models himself after his hero eg wolfe raises tropical flowers haig raises tropical fish they appeared in two subsequent decidedly tongueincheek mystery novels make out with murder and the topless tulip caper and a handful of short stories kelleredit four episodic novels hit man  hit list  hit parade  and hit me  as well as one fulllength novel hit and run  chronicle the life of keller a lonely wistful hitman who originally appeared as a semiregular feature in playboy magazine in the s most of the novels are fixups of related short stories hit and run is the only keller novel conceived of and written as a single story kellers full name is john paul keller a fact mentioned in hit man although he is rarely called anything but keller in the series the stories are rarely actionoriented or focused on the details of his crimes instead being character studies of kellers personality and the people he meets eg kellers being hired to kill a major league baseball designated hitter but postponing the act and following the team to away games so the hitter can reach the career milestone of  home runs originally based in new york city he later relocates to new orleans where he lives under the name nicholas edwards keller receives assignments via a contact named dot who is originally based in white plains his assignments usually take him to different cities where he often envisions himself retiring from the business daydreaming about settling there before finishing off the assignment and returning his fantasies forgotten as a passing dream kellers unlikely pastime is stamp collecting to which he is nearly obsessively devoted he collects nonus issues prior to  with a particular interest in stamps from former colonies of the french empire hit and run was nominated for the cwa gold dagger at the  crime thriller awards other worksedit small town  blocks first nonseries book in fifteen years details a group of new yorkers varying responses to the terrorist attacks of september   block has also written dozens of short stories over the years and he is the only fourtime winner of the edgar award for best short story the  collection enough rope compiles stories  in all from earlier collections such as like a lamb to slaughter and sometimes they bite along with new and previously uncollected stories block describes series character martin h ehrengraf as a dapper little criminal defense lawyer whose clients all turn out to be innocent ehrengraf charges a mere  retainer fee and afterwards works on contingency he gets paid a massive fee if and only if his clients are cleared of wrongdoing when his clients are cleared its because ehrengraf has committed misdeeds up to and including murder to exonerate his client and often frame another for the crimes the first short story featuring ehrengraf “the ehrengraf defense” was published in ellery queen’s mystery magazine in  by  twelve stories had been published and in  block completed an eleventh story “the ehrengraf settlement” all eleven were collected and published in an evolume ehrengraf for the defense  in addition to writing the scripts for a handful of television episodes over the years—including in  two episodes of the espn series tilt—block cowrote the screenplay for my blueberry nights a  film directed by wong karwai and starring norah jones selected bibliographyedit matthew scudder novelsedit the sins of the fathers  time to murder and create  in the midst of death  a stab in the dark  eight million ways to die  when the sacred ginmill closes  out on the cutting edge  a ticket to the boneyard  a dance at the slaughterhouse  a walk among the tombstones  the devil knows youre dead  a long line of dead men  even the wicked  everybody dies  hope to die  all the flowers are dying  a drop of the hard stuff  the night and the music  a collection of matthew scudder short stories and novelettes  in total bernie rhodenbarr novelsedit burglars cant be choosers  the burglar in the closet  the burglar who liked to quote kipling  the burglar who studied spinoza  the burglar who painted like mondrian  the burglar who traded ted williams  the burglar who thought he was bogart  the burglar in the library  the burglar in the rye  the burglar on the prowl  the burglar who counted the spoons  there are also three bernie rhodenbarr short stories like a thief in the night cosmopolitan may  the burglar who dropped in on elvis playboy april  and the burglar who smelled smoke mary higgins clark mystery magazine summerfall  these stories are collected in the  anthology enough rope evan tanner novelsedit the thief who couldnt sleep  the canceled czech  tanners twelve swingers  the scoreless thai aka two for tanner  tanners tiger  here comes a hero aka tanners virgin  me tanner you jane  tanner on ice  chip harrison novelsstories as chip harrisonedit no score  chip harrison scores again  make out with murder aka the five little rich girls  the topless tulip caper  as dark as christmas gets  a chip harrison short story written specifically for customers of the otto penzler–owned mysterious bookshop printed in booklet format for the  holiday season and collected in christmas at the mysterious bookshop vanguard press  isbn  a collection of eightyfour short stories enough rope  contains two chip harrison stories keller novelsedit hit man  hit list  hit parade  hit and run  hit me  a collection of eightyfour short stories enough rope  contains five keller stories written as jill emersonedit warm and willing  enough of sorrow  thirty  threesome  a madwomans diary  the trouble with eden  a week as andrea benstock  getting off  shadows  written as paul kavanaghedit such men are dangerous  the triumph of evil  not comin home to you  written as sheldon lordedit carla midwood books  born to be bad tower publications   barrow street tower publications  a strange kind of love tower publications  of shame and joy an original novel midwood books  a woman must love tower publications  midwood  kept tower publications  candy tower publications   gay street an original novel tower publications  april north softcover library  pads are for passion beacon press  reissued by hard case crime as a diet of treacle community of women beacon press  the sex shuffle universal publishing and distribution  reissued by hard case crime as lucky at cards savage lover softcover library  written in  reissued by hard case crime as sinner man pleasure machine midwood books  written as andrew shawedit sexpot by andrew shaw  illustration by harold w mccauley  campus tramp nightstand books  the adulterers corinth publications  high school sex club nightstand books  college for sinners corinth publications  sexpot nightstand books  the twisted ones nightstand books   lust corinth publications  reissued as cinderella sims by greenleaf classics gutter girl bedstand books  lover nightstand books  reissued as gigolo johnny wells sin devil nightstand books  four lives at the crossroads  written as don hollidayedit circle of sinners   in collaboration with hal dresner border lust  reissued by hard case crime as borderline written as lesley evansedit strange are the ways of love  written as lee duncanedit fidel castro assassinated  reissued by hard case crime as killing castro written as anne campbell clarkedit passport to peril  written as ben christopheredit strange embrace   originally written as a tiein to johnny midnight tv series in collaboration with donald e westlakeedit a girl called honey midwood books  credited to sheldon lord and alan marshall so willing midwood books  credited to sheldon lord and alan marshall sin hellcat nightstand books  credited to andrew shaw other fictionedit strange are the ways of love  as lesley evans reissued in  as shadows by jill emerson babe in the woods   block ghostwrote this novel following the death of author william ard only ard is credited death pulls a doublecross  reissued as cowards kiss mona  reissued as sweet slow death and by hard case crime as grifters game markham  reissued as you could call it murder  written and published as a tiein to markham tv series the girl with the long green heart  deadly honeymoon  after the first death  the specialists  ronald rabbit is a dirty old man  ariel  code of arms  into the night   block completed this novel from a manuscript by cornell woolrich random walk  small town  the girl with the deep blue eyes  short storiesedit some days you get the bear collected stories  enough rope collected stories  one night stands and lost weekends  dollys trash and treasures written for audio presentation in the sounds of crime  the night and the music  ehrengraf for the defense  catch and release  i know how to pick em  short story in anthology dangerous women  dark city lights new york stories  screenplayedit my blueberry nights  cowritten with wong karwai books for writersedit writing the novel from plot to print  telling lies for fun  profit  a collection of his slightly reedited fiction howto column from writers digest write for your life  spider spin me a web  the liars bible  the liars companion  afterthoughts  writing the novel from plot to print to pixel  memoirsedit step by step a pedestrian memoir  awards and nominationsedit wins are in bold anthony awardsedit  best novel when the sacred ginmill closes  best novel a ticket to the boneyard  best short story collection some days you get the bear  best short story collection masters choice ii edgar awardsedit  best paperback original time to murder and create  best novel eight million ways to die  best short story by dawns early light  best short story answers to soldier  best novel a dance at the slaughterhouse best short story a blow for freedom  grand master award best short story kellers therapy  best novel a long lin